      },
      "description": "Hear me out on this one peeps. after alice's significant revamp ive done sum experimenting with a modernized kit. Alice traded her mana bar for massive HP-scaling and initiation power so my build focuses solely on Raw HP, Healing Amplification and % Damage.  Alice no longer relies on mana items like CoD or the Purple buff to maintain her ult and skills so we now the only bottleneck was CD....fleeting time deals with this. Oracle is non negotiable synergizing with her new passive boosting healing drastically. Guardian Helmet for her hybrid durability as her damage and healing now scale with extra HP....if your about to die, pop open your passive on some minions and wallah your near full health again. Alice's ult provides control immunity and 50% damage reduction, but she is slowed during the ult, becoming a primary target during the Ult's charge. Winter crown cancels this weakness allowing you to stay invincible while your ult charges and crashes onto the enemy team. Her skill one has wide range why not add a slow effect to it to ensure enemies cannot walk away after that blood stream, then you teleport and ult and the enemy team is wiped out....Ice queen wand handles this like a goat. And finally Her second skills synergy with HP Based scorch of glowing wand. come on ifykykwim glowing wand adding a burn effect to the skill 2 and passive. Its like a double scorch alone brother. Flicker is nice but Vengeance is greater for damage reductions and reflecting magic damage when you're constantly in the enemy's face. And the tank emblem is superior for Max HP and Hybrid defense",
